","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","about 1500":"about 1500","1 January 1460":"1 January 1460","1460":"1460","22 October 1488":"22 October 1488","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Peebles, Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Baird","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish:","from a common pronunciation of   Bard   in Scotland.","occupational name from Gaelic <i>bàrd</i> ‘bard, poet, minstrel’, or of Gaelic <b>Mac an Baird</b> ‘son of the bard’."],"variants":[{"name":"Beaird","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Baird  ."]},{"name":"Bard","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Michel, Aime, Alphonse, Alphy, Armand, Cecile, Celestine, Emile, Fernand, Germaine, Gilles, Jacques.","English (of Norman origin) and French: from the Old French personal name <i>Bard(e)</i>, ancient Germanic <i>Bardo</i>, from <i>barta</i> ‘battle axe’. This was borne as a surname by a prominent Norman family with lands in west Normandy and in various English and Scottish counties, including Essex, Hertfordshire, North Yorkshire, Northumberland, and Lanarkshire. In Scotland the original family were Norman landowners in Strathaven parish in Lanarkshire. They were descended from the Baards, lords of Loftus in the North Yorkshire, descendants of the mid 12th-century Richard <i>Baart</i>.","Irish: altered form of either   Beard   or   Baird  ."]}]},{"name":"Gilbert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Old French name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. This was the name of the founder of the only native British religious order (abolished at the Dissolution of the Monasteries),  St Gilbert  of Sempringham (  ?1083–1189 ), in whose honour it is still sometimes bestowed, especially among Roman Catholics. It gained a wider currency in the 19th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Gilbert Baird I was born in 1434, in Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland, his father, Sir Gavin Baird of Posso, was 34 and his mother, Elizabeth Gordon, was 25. He married Lilly Baird of Ordinhivas on 22 October 1488, in Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1503, in his hometown, at the age of 69, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"1434–1503":"1434–1503","1434–1513":"1434–1513","1460–1513":"1460–1513","1400–1478":"1400–1478","1410–1500":"1410–1500","1503":"1503","1513":"1513","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","about 1500":"umbes 1500","1 January 1460":"1. jaanuar 1460","1460":"1460","22 October 1488":"22. oktoober 1488","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Peebles, Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1434–1503":"1434–1503","1434–1513":"1434–1513","1460–1513":"1460–1513","1400–1478":"1400–1478","1410–1500":"1410–1500","1503":"1503","1513":"1513","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","about 1500":"noin 1500","1 January 1460":"1. tammikuuta 1460","1460":"1460","22 October 1488":"22. lokakuuta 1488","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Peebles, Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1434–1503":"1434–1503","1434–1513":"1434–1513","1460–1513":"1460–1513","1400–1478":"1400–1478","1410–1500":"1410–1500","1503":"1503","1513":"1513","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","about 1500":"environ 1500","1 January 1460":"1 janvier 1460","1460":"1460","22 October 1488":"22 octobre 1488","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Valle de Twede, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","Peebles, Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peebles, Valle de Twede, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Sir Gilbert Baird I est né en 1434, à Peebles, Valle de Twede, Écosse, son père, Sir Gavin Baird of Posso, avait 34 ans et sa mère, Elizabeth Gordon, avait 25 ans. Il a épousé Lilly Baird of Ordinhivas le 22 octobre 1488, à Peebles, Valle de Twede, Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé en 1503, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 69 ans, et a été enterré à Écosse."},"de":{"1434–1503":"1434–1503","1434–1513":"1434–1513","1460–1513":"1460–1513","1400–1478":"1400–1478","1410–1500":"1410–1500","1503":"1503","1513":"1513","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","about 1500":"um 1500","1 January 1460":"1. Januar 1460","1460":"1460","22 October 1488":"22. Oktober 1488","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Peebles, Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Als Sir Gilbert Baird I 1434 in Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland geboren wurde, war sein Vater Sir Gavin Baird of Posso 34 und seine Mutter Elizabeth Gordon 25. Er hat am 22. Oktober 1488 in Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland Lilly Baird of Ordinhivas geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1503 im Alter von 69 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort und wurde in Scotland begraben."},"ht":{"1434–1503":"1434–1503","1434–1513":"1434–1513","1460–1513":"1460–1513","1400–1478":"1400–1478","1410–1500":"1410–1500","1503":"1503","1513":"1513","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","about 1500":"about 1500","1 January 1460":"1 January 1460","1460":"1460","22 October 1488":"22 October 1488","Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peeblesshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Peebles, Peebles-shire, Scotland":"Peebles, Peeblesshire, Scotland"},"hu":{"1434–1503":"1434–1503","1434–1513":"1434–1513","1460–1513":"1460–1513","1400–1478":"1400–1478","1410–1500":"1410–1500","1503":"1503","1513":"1513","1434":"1434","1478":"1478","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","1410":"1410","about 1500":"1500 körül","1 